From e8cf2ae6daaf86f0dea902760240345e5e5df085 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 11:31:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] panfrost: enable blit-based texture transfers

Advertise PIPE_TEXTURE_TRANSFER_BLIT for Panfrost texture transfers.

The previous commit keeps shader image masks in sync while unbinding.
That avoids the NULL image crash seen while testing this path.

Tested on a Rock 5B with Mali-G610/Panthor using Piglit getteximage,
PBO, and readpixels coverage.

Assisted-by: OpenAI Codex GPT-5.5
---
ARCHIVE ANNOTATION (not part of the commit; `git am` ignores this block)

Purpose: REPRODUCTION ONLY, not for merging. This is the patch that makes
Panfrost take the sampled-BLIT texture-transfer path, which is required to
reproduce the BLIT failure in repro_blit.c and the BLIT column of the
bench_transfer.c timing table in ../validation.md. Once upstream ships a
non-BLIT default, this configuration cannot be rebuilt from upstream alone.

Provenance:
- Exported verbatim via `git format-patch -1 e8cf2ae6daa` from the local
  Mesa working tree (/home/yi/Code/mesa, remote github.com/yisding/mesa),
  branch panfrost-transfer-blit, on 2026-07-01.
- It advertises PIPE_TEXTURE_TRANSFER_BLIT only (no local commit ever
  advertised BLIT|COMPUTE). The COMPUTE side of every BLIT-vs-COMPUTE
  comparison was produced on this same build by forcing the compute path
  with MESA_COMPUTE_PBO=1 -- see ../validation.md and README.md here.
- Base: applies on top of "panfrost: clear shader image mask on trailing
  unbinds" (local 950d19686d8, Fixes: 72ff66c3d73), itself on Mesa main
  c05334058d5 (2026-06-22, 26.2-devel). Without the mask fix, compute
  transfer testing can hit a NULL image-resource dereference.
- The commit message's "Tested ... Piglit" claim predates the discovery
  that BLIT is NOT bit-exact for integer format-changing transfers on
  Mali-G610 (see ../blit-precision.md). Do not read it as an endorsement.

Disassembly capture: the Valhall asm listings in ../blit-precision.md and
../README.md were captured from a build with this patch applied by running
the failing case with BIFROST_MESA_DEBUG=shaders (src/panfrost/compiler/
bifrost/bi_debug.c; dumps NIR, BIR, and the final packed Valhall asm to
stderr) and taking the u_blitter TXF fragment shader (named "TTN1").
Note: PAN_MESA_DEBUG is a different variable (driver-level toggles such as
nofp16/linear/sync); the compiler dump flag is BIFROST_MESA_DEBUG=shaders.

 src/gallium/drivers/panfrost/pan_screen.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/gallium/drivers/panfrost/pan_screen.c b/src/gallium/drivers/panfrost/pan_screen.c
index 274053f6550..789b8de7e6c 100644
--- a/src/gallium/drivers/panfrost/pan_screen.c
+++ b/src/gallium/drivers/panfrost/pan_screen.c
@@ -826,7 +826,7 @@ panfrost_init_screen_caps(struct panfrost_screen *screen)
 
    caps->max_vertex_element_src_offset = 0xffff;
 
-   caps->texture_transfer_modes = 0;
+   caps->texture_transfer_modes = PIPE_TEXTURE_TRANSFER_BLIT;
 
    caps->endianness = PIPE_ENDIAN_NATIVE;
 
